00.

Last year I went to a concert of my favorite singer in Georgia with my friends after which we've met a Russian guy who invited us to the karaoke bar where he worked. We went there and sang this song. At first I forgot about it, but about a month after it started playing in my head, I started listening to it every day and realized that it strikes me so much I can't even say it with words and that I can't live without it, especially since I've learnt the story of it and it's author. Now I know every Amy's song, she is the person that helped me get through the past year, my second favorite singer and someone I never knew but somehow feel deep emotional connection with. I also consider her one of the best artists of her time, the music is so unique.



13.

Well, I wanted to choose something in English and so I thought about this song because a lot of times when I party with my friends we end up screaming this on the night streets or at someone's balcony. I feel that the song is important because all my friends have different taste in music but still can share the feeling of the song - so the feeling must be really common and touching, which are always the most important ones.



05.

I sometimes get sentimental and like to think about the things that unite society and that people from different parts of the world can share and feel together. For example, if you put mothers from all the countries into one room - they'll definitely start discussing their children; if you put together their children - they will just start playing together despite of all the language and cultural barriers. When I saw the word "society" I started to think about a song that both made a change in Western music and is loved and listened to by the most different units of the society, about a really important one. Therefore I remembered this song and that I've sung it on a music lesson at primary school, with my friends, at an international summer camp and even with my grandmother - so I decided to choose it because it's so universal and valuable.
